      "resolution_level": 5,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_psychology_neuroscience_l3_anxiety_disorders",
      "content": {
        "title": "Acute Panic Attack Management",
        "definition": "Immediate clinical approach to a panic attack including reassurance, breathing techniques, ruling out medical emergencies, and judicious short-acting anxiolytic use when appropriate.",
        "summary": "Acute management focuses on safety, reassurance, and exclusion of cardiac or metabolic mimics. Long-term treatment targets panic disorder prevention rather than repeated rescue sedation."
      },
